## Retrieval‑Augmented Generation (RAG)

Retrieval‑Augmented Generation (RAG) is a hybrid architecture that couples a **retriever** with a **generator** so a language model can ground its output in up‑to‑date external knowledge rather than relying solely on pre‑training data [1].

### Core Components
| Component | Role |
|-----------|------|
| External knowledge source | Documents, APIs, or databases containing factual material. |
| Text chunking & preprocessing | Splits large texts into manageable pieces and normalises them. |
| Embedding model | Converts each chunk into a dense vector representing its semantic meaning. |
| Vector database | Stores vectors and enables fast similarity search
```

